Hello! I would like to get the attention of the devs about an issue that currently makes `MouseState` unusable. I'm using the latest dev build of MonoGame, `3.5.0.574`, I believe? So here's an example code:

``` c#
protected Texture2D cursorTex;
protected Rectangle cursorRect;
protected MouseState mouseState;

public virtual void LoadContent(ContentManager Content)
{
    content = new ContentManager(Content.ServiceProvider, "Content");
    cursorTex = content.Load<Texture2D>(@"Graphics/Cursors/cursor_0");
}

public virtual void Update(GameTime gameTime)
{
    mouseState = Mouse.GetState();
    cursorRect = new Rectangle(mouseState.X, mouseState.Y, cursorTex.Width, cursorTex.Height);
}

public virtual void Draw(SpriteBatch spriteBatch)
{
    spriteBatch.Draw(cursorTex, cursorRect, Color.White);
}
```

Above, I am trying to create a custom cursor for my game. But when I debug, the cursor image stays at the `0, 0` coordinates of the screen and won't move. Could the image be the problem? It is a BMP file 32x32 pixels with magenta background for transparency.

Why do `Mouse.GetState().X` and `Mouse.GetState().Y` always return `0, 0`? I tested this exact same code in XNA and it worked (although my cursor texture had offset compared to the default windows mouse pointer). In my override methods I call `base.LoadContent(Content);`, `base.Update(gameTime);` and `base.Draw(spriteBatch);` and everything else works except the cursor. Did it work before? What was the default behavior? Can a developer test the issue as well?
